nodes.text: Amphibians were species that could live both on land and underwater, or had two stages of life, one that is completely water-based, the other land-based. Some amphibious creatures were born as gill-breathing tadpoles and evolved into air-breathing adults. Others had compound lungs allowing them to breathe underwater and on land. The Shawda Ubb of the planet Manpha were amphibians, as were the Nautolans of Glee Anselm, the Aqualish of Ando, the Mon Calamari and Quarren of Dac, the Gungans of Naboo and the Ootoolans of Ootoola.
